Twenty-six-year-old rising music star, Bella Abidemi Oluwasegun aka Bellamino has released a new Afropop single entitled: Pepper Soup. Currently signed to Akwaamaka Record Label, Bellamino’s new single is coming after he broke into the music scene with his debut single Come Online a few years back.   Marriage? Count me out, says Iyabo Ojo     Teni Makanaki thrills at Gbenga Adeyinka’s Laffmattazz show     I can’t date a lady who asks me out, says Ugovin   While confident about his new song, Bellamino says Pepper Soup will create the feeling that comes with the African cuisine when listening to the new single. The indigene of Abigi local government area of Ogun State has displayed his readiness to remain in the industry with the fourth single. While he says fans should expect his upcoming EP, Bellamino is confident that his style and lyrics will continue to make way for him as it has done with songs like Respond, Destiny, Come Online, and now Pepper Soup.